<h2 style="margin:0 0 16px;font-size:20px;font-weight:600;color:#111;line-height:1.3;">
  {{ notification.title | e }}
</h2>

<p style="margin:0 0 20px;font-size:15px;line-height:1.6;color:#374151;">
  {{ notification.body | e }}
</p>

<p style="margin:0 0 20px;padding:14px;background:#fef3c7;border-left:3px solid #f59e0b;font-size:14px;color:#78350f;line-height:1.5;">
  <strong>Heads up:</strong> a CameraNode going offline means every
  camera attached to it has also gone dark. Cameras will appear
  offline in the dashboard until the node reconnects.
</p>

<p style="margin:0 0 8px;font-size:14px;color:#6b7280;font-weight:600;">
  Common causes
</p>
<ul style="margin:0 0 24px;padding-left:20px;font-size:14px;line-height:1.6;color:#374151;">
  <li>The host machine crashed, lost power, or was rebooted.</li>
  <li>The systemd service / Windows Service stopped (check the host).</li>
  <li>The host lost internet connectivity entirely.</li>
</ul>

<table role="presentation" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0">
  <tr>
    <td style="background:#22c55e;border-radius:6px;">
      <a href="{{ dashboard_url }}/admin"
         style="display:inline-block;padding:10px 18px;font-size:14px;font-weight:600;color:#0a0a0f;text-decoration:none;">
        Open admin panel →
      </a>
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>

<p style="margin:24px 0 0;font-size:13px;color:#9ca3af;line-height:1.5;">
  This alert went only to organization admins.
</p>
